<stack-static>
    <statement><p><h3 style="text-align:center;">
Expand and simplify the following expression:
</h3>

<p style="text-align:center;">
<me>
({1}x + {-3})({4}x + {-1})
</me>
</p>

<p style="text-align:center;">
Give your answer in the form <m>Ax^2 + Bx + C</m>.
</p>

<p style="text-align:center;">
<fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>To expand the product of two binomials, we use the distributive property 
(multiply each term in the first bracket by each term in the second bracket).</p>

<p>
<m>
({1}x + {-3})({4}x + {-1})
</m>
</p>

<p>Multiply each term:</p>

<p>
<m>
= ({1}x)({4}x) + ({1}x)({-1}) + ({-3})({4}x) + ({-3})({-1})
</m>
</p>

<p>Simplify each product:</p>

<p>
<m>
= {4}x^2 + {-1}x + {-12}x + {3}
</m>
</p>

<p>Now combine like terms:</p>

<p>
<m>
= {4}x^2 + {-13}x + {3}
</m>
</p>

<p><alert>Final Answer:</alert></p>

<p>
<m>
{4 x^2-13 x+3}
</m>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>4 x^2-13 x+3</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>